Yeah, Amumu's build versatility is fantastic and lets him suit a lot of team compositions.

Your team is heavy AD with another tank/bruiser?  
{{item:3020}} {{item:3725}} {{item:3116}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3001}} {{item:3151}} 

Team is damage heavy and needs a tank with CC to engage/peel?
{{item:3158}} {{item:3725}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3102}} {{item:3151}} {{item:3110}} or {{item:3075}} 

Enemy team has several tanks?
{{item:3020}} {{item:3725}} {{item:3143}} {{item:3102}} {{item:3151}} {{item:3135}} 

And Amumu's ability to hard-engage or peel enemies, clear the jungle and objective monsters quickly, good early ganks, and damage both tanks and squishies are valuable in pretty much every team composition.  He's rarely a bad pick, if you aren't too worried about early invades or believe you can survive them.
